Sentencas: An overpotential model for planar solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) is developed and applied to the numerical simulation of a stack.
Titulo: Charge-transfer distribution model applicable to stack simulation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Charge-transfer distributions within the electrodes are approximated using an exponential function, based on which the ohmic loss and activation overpotential are evaluated.
Titulo: Charge-transfer distribution model applicable to stack simulation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The predicted current-voltage characteristics are in good agreement with the experimental results.
Titulo: Charge-transfer distribution model applicable to stack simulation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the overpotentials within the cell can reproduce the results obtained from a numerical analysis where the distribution of the charge-transfer current within the electrodes is fully solved.
Titulo: Charge-transfer distribution model applicable to stack simulation of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The proposed model is expected to be useful for maintaining the accuracy of SOFC simulations when the cell components, consisting of the anode, electrolyte and cathode, are simplified into a single-layer element.
Titulo: Charge-transfer distribution model applicable to stack simulation of solid oxide fuel cells
